abstract: Why 15 percent is so important to him, and how Bloomberg could scramble those calculations.
snippet: Why 15 percent is so important to him, and how Bloomberg could scramble those calculations.
lead_paragraph: The results of the Iowa and New Hampshire contests amount to a strategic victory for Bernie Sanders, fracturing his opposition and opening a path for him to win the nomination.

abstract: California billionaire Tom Steyer said Wednesday he's poised to “shock the world” next week with a good showing in the Nevada caucuses, which he says is necessary for him to eventually win a “wide open” race for the Democratic presidential nomination.
snippet: California billionaire Tom Steyer said Wednesday he's poised to “shock the world” next week with a good showing in the Nevada caucuses, which he says is necessary for him to eventually win a “wide open” race for the Democratic presidential nominat...
lead_paragraph: RENO, Nev. — California billionaire Tom Steyer said Wednesday he's poised to “shock the world” next week with a good showing in the Nevada caucuses, which he says is necessary for him to eventually win a “wide open” race for the Democratic presidential nomination.
headline_main: Steyer Ready to 'Shock the World' in Nevada's Wide-Open Race

abstract: She said she did not want to “burn down the rest of the party” in order to triumph. And then she lost in New Hampshire.
snippet: She said she did not want to “burn down the rest of the party” in order to triumph. And then she lost in New Hampshire.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — It was 24 hours before the biggest contest of her political life. Senator Elizabeth Warren didn’t want to talk about it that way.

abstract: Nevada Democrats will use scannable paper ballots for early voting in their caucuses after problems with an app plunged Iowa's nominating contest into chaos last week, according to a state party memo sent to presidential campaigns.
snippet: Nevada Democrats will use scannable paper ballots for early voting in their caucuses after problems with an app plunged Iowa's nominating contest into chaos last week, according to a state party memo sent to presidential campaigns.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Nevada Democrats will use scannable paper ballots for early voting in their caucuses after problems with an app plunged Iowa's nominating contest into chaos last week, according to a state party memo sent to presidential campaigns.
headline_main: After Iowa Meltdown, Nevada Democrats Will Use Scannable Early Voting Ballots
headline_print_headline: After Iowa Meltdown, Nevada Democrats Will Use Scannable Early Voting Ballots

abstract: Lawmakers who flipped Republican districts in 2018 worry that a democratic socialist at the top of the ticket could doom their re-election chances.
snippet: Lawmakers who flipped Republican districts in 2018 worry that a democratic socialist at the top of the ticket could doom their re-election chances.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As Bernie Sanders emerges as the leader in the race for the Democratic presidential nomination, his rise is generating fears among centrist Democrats that the apparent leftward shift of their party could cost them not only a chance to retake the White House, but also their hold on the majority in the House of Representatives and their shot at winning the Senate.

headline_main: Moderate Democrats Fear Bernie Sanders Could Cost Them the House

abstract: As the 2020 candidates vie for support in South Carolina, Mr. Steyer has been criticized for hiring black lawmakers or their companies. Records show the Sanders campaign has done the same.
snippet: As the 2020 candidates vie for support in South Carolina, Mr. Steyer has been criticized for hiring black lawmakers or their companies. Records show the Sanders campaign has done the same.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Last April, just as the 2020 presidential campaign was getting underway, Senator Bernie Sanders trumpeted a breakthrough in his campaign’s quest for black voters’ support in South Carolina.
